The paper focuses on analyzing the behavior of self-interested users in online communities and designing social norms to ensure cooperation. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the adaptation of strategies by users, which can be related to reinforcement learning (cs.LG) and control theory (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic processes, which can be related to information theory (cs.IT) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
